    <h4 class="pinstall">Setup</h4>
    <ol class="ollatency">
        <li>
            Install the db from the terminal.
        </li>
        <div class="installcomands"><p> npm install lowdb</p></div>
        <li> Copy the db folder to you project.</li>
        <div class="installcomands"><p> copy ./src/database/folder </p></div>
        <li> Copy the survey folder to your project and give it a suggestive name.</li>
        <div class="installcomands"><p> copy ./src/stages/survey/ </p></div>
        <li>Now, you need to import the database, the survey and commands in server.js file.</li>
        <div class="installcomands"><p> import {DatabaseHandler} from './src/database/DatabaseHandler' </p>
                                    <p> import survey from './src/stages/survey/server/server'</p>
                                    <p> let commands = {
                                        'reqJSON': (server, clientId) => {
                                        let json = DatabaseHandler.exportAsJSON()
                                        server.send('resJSON', json).toAdmin()
                                        },</p>
                                     <p> 'reqCSV': (server, clientId) => {
                                          let csv = DatabaseHandler.exportAsCSV()
                                         server.send('resCSV', csv).toAdmin()
                                         }  </p>
        </div>
        <li>In the admin-client.hmtl file, you will need to add the html button for json and csv files. In admin-client.js you need to add the listener
            and the events.
        </li>
        <div class="installcomands"><p> $('#admin-button-download-json').mouseup(e => {
                e.preventDefault()
                admin.sendCommand('reqJSON')
                })</p>
        <p> $('#admin-button-download-csv').mouseup(e => {
            e.preventDefault()
            admin.sendCommand('reqCSV')
            })</p>
        <p> let events = {
            'resJSON': (admin, json) => {
            let fileName = 'monsterr-modules_' + Date.now() + '.csv'
            let data = JSON.stringify(json)
            let url = window.URL.createObjectURL(new Blob([data], {type: 'text/json'}))
            var a = document.createElement('a')
            document.body.appendChild(a)
            a.style = 'display: none'
            a.href = url
            a.download = fileName
            a.click()
            window.URL.revokeObjectURL(url)
            },</p>
        </div>
    </ol>
